    ----------
    value : float

    Notes
    -----
    The log-cdf of a gamma distribution is defined as the following expression:
    .. math::
        \log(x) = \log(h) + \log(z) + \log(x - 1) - \log(x) + \log(x + 1) - \log(x + 1) - \log(x - 1)
    where :math:`x` is the value of the function.

Static file serving.
    
    This is a very simple file serving middleware. It serves static files
    from a directory or a file.
    
    The file serving is done by opening the file and reading it.
    
    The file is served with the Content-Type header set to the mimetype
    of the file.
    
    If the file is a directory, it is served with a list of files in the
    directory.
    
    If the file is a symlink, it is served by following the symlink.
    
    If the file is a directory and the directory is empty, an empty file
    is served.
    
    If the file is a directory and the directory is not empty, an error is
    raised.
    
    If the file is a directory and the directory is not empty and the
    directory is not a symlink, a 404 error is raised.
    
    If the file is a directory and the directory is not empty and the
    directory is a symlink, a 403 error is raised.
